node.title: Betty White, legendary actress and icon, has died at 99
node.description: The beloved TV star's career, which included major roles in The Mary Tyler Moore Show and The Golden Girls, kicked off in 1949.
node.content: ["Beloved actress and cultural icon Betty White has died, her agent and close friend Jeff Witjas told People. She was 99, just a few weeks shy of what would have been her 100th birthday on January 17.", "\"Even though Betty was about to be 100, I thought she would live forever,\" Witjas said to People in a statement. \"I will miss her terribly and so will the animal world that she loved so much. I don't think Betty ever feared passing because she always wanted to be with her most beloved husband Allen Ludden. She believed she would be with him again.\"\u00a0", "For Breaking News & Analysis Download the Free CBS News app"]
